Traditional and Alternative Services

We can plan conventional funerary services which stick to widely recognized, ceremonial customs. Traditional funerary services, while flexible, often contain ministry services in a nearby church and a hearse led funeral procession. All the details of the ceremony will be determined by whether or not faith plays a role, but the important point is that you have a selection. Alternate services are growing in popularity as more and more are choosing to personalize the ceremony for their deceased loved ones, a celebration of life as opposed to a confrontation of death. Secular and Celebrant Services

Funeral Directors Available 24 Hours a Day
